RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 54. Maiden Claiming Purse 10800. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOLY HIP took the lead nearing the seven sixteenths pole and set a pressured pace, raced at the rail on the turn and was steadily handled in the lane. ROBBEDINTHEBAHAMAS steadied leaving the gate then picked up the chase, raced four wide on the turn and settled for second best. FLASH OF DAY gave chase inside, rounded the turn near the rail and flattened in the lane. FIDDLERSHOTPLEASUR chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. BUFF'S CAT pressured the pace through the backstretch, raced close in the three path on the turn then weakened. MONEY MAC chased, angled to the six path through the turn and showed little in the stretch. ARMY BEAUTY was kept in check while racing wide through the backstretch and was eased in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Holy Hip
ENTRY.OWNER: C M Racing Stables LLC and Lewis Jalen
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,rail turn,steadily handled lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 54. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALERA LOVE took over nearing the seven sixteenths pole and rated the early pace, came under pressure toward the quarter pole, rounded the turn at the rail and was steadily handled in the stretch. CLARIFICATION gave chase after a brief early lead, raced off the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. UNCONSCIOUS MIND was bumped leaving the gate then gave chase, raced three wide on the turn then flattened in the stretch. DOLCE ON THE ROCKS chased outside, rounded the turn in the five path and passed rivals widest. EBONY QUEEN became a bit anxious in the gate, gave chase inside and showed little in the lane. AZTECA GIRL gave chase inside, raced near the rail on the turn and weakened. SECRET MOMENT broke outward and made contact with Unconscious Mind and never factored.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Twin Creeks Farm, Dennis Steger & Steve& Melody Golding

ENTRY.NAME: Ebony Queen
ENTRY.COMMENT: anxious in gate,chased inside,rail turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 98. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 29400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. No n-winners Of A Race Since August 22 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COWAN came out at the break and made contact with Jungle Beast, raced in the five path the first turn, picked up the chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole and took aim in the three path nearing the quarter, dug in determinedly leaving the turn and edged out ALPHA CHI RHO through the final sixteenth. The latter rated close in the three path, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole and took the lead three wide approaching the quarter, raced briefly clear midway on the far turn but was met leaving the turn and dueled gamely to mid-stretch before reluctantly ceding. O'CONNER SUNSET rounded the first turn in the three path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and dug in to hold third. JUNGLE BEAST was bumped leaving the gate then saved ground on the opening turn, eased out into the backstretch, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the four path and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. LIKEABLE set the early pace inside, was met approaching the nine sixteenths pole and dueled at mostly even terms from that point, but dropped back past the five sixteenths and faded at the rail on the far turn. ICING rated close two deep on the first turn and moved to even terms past the nine sixteenths pole, but dropped back at the quarter pole and faded at the rail on the far turn. MARTINKELLY was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Icing
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close 2d 1st turn,even terms past 9/16,met toward 1/4,faded

ENTRY.NAME: Martinkelly
ENTRY.OWNER: Two Ten Twelve Triple T Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAKE YOUR TIME took the lead leaving the chute and rated the early pace, came under pressure past the five sixteenths pole, rounded the turn near the rail and held well under steady handling. GOLD CREATIONS gave chase and raced close in the three path on the turn, couldn't match strides with the winner but cleared second later yards. AYE CALYPSO gave chase, raced close at the rail on the turn then flattened inside the eighth pole. GOOD BUZZ gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn at the rail, eased out past the eighth pole and finished well. ESTRELLA FUGAZ chased outside, rounded the turn about the four path, drifted leaving the turn and ran evenly in the lane. GREATEST NOTION came away awkwardly and hit the gate but gave chase through the backstretch, raced close two deep while between horses on the turn then weakened into the lane. YES MY PRINCE chased, raced off the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. I'MLIVINGTHEDREAM came away awkwardly and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: I'mlivingthedream
ENTRY.OWNER: Mountain View Racing LLC and Golden Melinda B

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Purse 31300. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 22 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 22 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOONLIT SHADOW raced with the pace two deep through the front stretch, took the nod leaving the nine sixteenths pole and dueled Full Moon Lover at mostly even terms from that point, contested the far turn between horses and dug in determinedly to edge out LUCYLOU WHO through the stretch. The latter stalked from the three path the first turn, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole, drew to even terms three wide midway on the far turn and dug in gamely to the finish. CHANGE THE WORLD saved early ground then picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, eased outward into the lane and finished well to take third later yards. FULL MOON LOVER raced with the early pace, was met leaving the nine sixteenths pole and gave close chase from that point, contested even terms at the rail on the far turn but weakened inside the eighth pole. LUCKY BLONDE raced off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, eased outward leaving the turn and showed little further. SENECA ROCKS rounded the opening turn about the four path and showed little response through the backstretch. JAMESTOWN ROAD saved ground on the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Change the World
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 7/16,off rail turn,finished well,up 3rd late

ENTRY.NAME: Full Moon Lover
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

ENTRY.NAME: Lucky Blonde
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,chased 7/16,rail far turn,eased out 1/8,empty lane

ENTRY.NAME: Moonlit Shadow
ENTRY.COMMENT: w/pace,nod past 9/16,even terms between turn,determinedly lane

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Timothy C. Grams & Judith A. Grams

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 73. Allowance Purse 27400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 22 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 22 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12, 500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'M THE MONEY MAN tapered in and stalked the early pace two deep, took the nod into the backstretch and kept the edge over Bop Zapper from the half mile pole, cleared that one past the five sixteenths, contested the edge at the rail on the far turn, moved clear past the eighth pole and held on well with steady handling. SUMMONING DENIS raced off the rail on the first turn then eased outward into the backstretch, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, drew to even terms two deep past the quarter but dropped back leaving the eighth pole and had to settle for second best. O'RIGSBY saved ground well off the pace on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and finished evenly to take third inside the sixteenth pole. CIDERHOUSE WAY settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn then flattened inside the eighth pole. SCARE DEM raced in the three path the first turn, eased out into the backstretch and gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the five path and showed little more. CHASENJOHNATHAN rated close to the early pace inside, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and weakened in the lane. LIEUTENANT BROWN hopped at the break and raced well back. BOP ZAPPER took the early lead and moved to the inside to show the way, was met approaching the half mile pole and gave chase through the backstretch but faded at the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: O'Rigsby
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 3/8,off rail far turn,even finish

ENTRY.NAME: Bop Zapper
ENTRY.COMMENT: early lead inside,met 1/2,chased,faded rail far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Scare Dem
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3p 1st turn,eased out 1/2,chased past 7/16,5p far turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Rachel's Turn S. CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR REGISTERED ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA BRED FILLIES TWO YEAR OLDS. $50 nominations close Tuesday, September 12, 2023. $50 to enter with a purse of $75,000 Added. Entries close Tuesday, September 19, 2023 by the usual time of closing. The added monies an d all fees to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weight: 120 lbs. Field will be limited to ten starters with up to four alternates. Preference to those horses having accumulated the highest career e arnings at the time of closing of entries. Trophy to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIRECT THE CAT took a quick lead, cleared the field and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure past the five sixteenths pole, drew off at the rail on the turn and was kept alert while proving much the best. RAN OUT OF TRAINER chased outside through most of the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn, drifted leaving the turn and settled for second best. NAVY BAND came away awkwardly and was jostled between horses on the chute, gave chase toward the inside, raced in the four path on the turn but was carried out entering the lane and showed little more. MAMA MARGE chased inside through the backstretch, angled out approaching the head of the lane and weakened. ILIKEFUNSIZE exchanged contact with Navy Band leaving the gate then gave chase inside, rounded the turn near the rail and showed little in the lane. MAD SWANN exchanged contact with Navy Band leaving the gate then gave chase but weakened off the rail on the turn. SEVEN NATTY PATTY showed little and was not encouraged leaving the turn.

ENTRY.OWNER: Baccari Racing Stable LLC and Dream Walkin Farms Inc

ENTRY.NAME: Ilikefunsize
ENTRY.OWNER: Burnsworth Richard and Five Hellions Farm

ENTRY.COMMENT: quickly cleared,rated pace inside,drew off turn,kept alert

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY BUDDY DUANE checked off the heels of Aldarighttricks midway on the opening turn then altered course and took over two deep at the three eighths pole, contested the advantage nearest the rail on the far turn and was steadily handled to late stretch. JUST CALL ME AL settled off the rail on the opening turn then gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced close off the rail on the far turn but had to settle for second best. GREATANDGOOD rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole, came through the far turn in the three path then flattened into the lane. LORD CLANCY saved ground off the pace, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole and improved in the four path on the far turn, but showed little further. JUST MURPHY settled two deep on the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and weakened in the stretch. ALDARIGHTTRICKS closed to the lead at the three quarter pole while tapering inward, moved to the rail midway on the opening turn, was met at the three eighths, dropped back from the five sixteenths pole and gave way at the rail into the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: My Buddy Duane
ENTRY.COMMENT: checked rail 1st turn,up 2d 3/8,edge rail turn,in hand late
